The Commissioner for Water Resources Development, Delta State, Rt. Hon. Evelyn Omavowan Oboro Esq., has joined family members, associates and well-wishers to celebrate Hon. Ramson Tega Onoyake, Executive Chairman, Uvwie Local Government Council on the auspicious occasion of his birthday anniversary. Oboro, a former House of Representatives member and Delta Central Senatorial Candidate of the PDP in the last general elections, said it was heartwarming to celebrate a dynamic and administrator per excellence who has shown capacity in managing the affairs of Uvwie Local Government Council to the admiration of the people. She noted that it was these qualities amongst others that endeared the people of Uvwie Local Government Area to vote him for a second term as Uvwie Local Government chairman, which made him to be the first Local Government Council chairman to be elected for a second term in Uvwie. Oboro Congratulates Ibori At 63, Hails Oyovbaire As He Clocks 80 Delta Commissioner Felicitates With Jite Brown On His Birthday… Oboro described him as an outstanding personality, a gentleman, God-fearing human, philanthropist and encourager of the downtrodden. “On behalf of my family, friends and associates, I felicitate with and congratulate, Hon. Ramson Tega Onoyake, the executive chairman, Uvwie Local Government Council; wishing him an outstanding, blessed, highly favoured, fruitful, joyous and fun-filled birthday celebration. I pray that God grant him more years ahead in good health and prosperity”, she added.